# Frontend (Angular) Rules

## Scope
- UI lives in `apps/frontend`.
- `apps/api` is backend/API only.

## Angular Structure
- Keep feature logic in Angular components/services/modules under `apps/frontend/src`.
- Keep HTTP calls in frontend services, not inside presentational components when avoidable.
- Keep route-driven pages in Angular router; backend should expose JSON endpoints only.

## API Integration
- Consume backend routes with their prefixes (`/auth/*`, `/v1/*`, `/admin/*`).
- Send JWT as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` for protected routes.
- Handle auth and API errors in frontend state/UI, not in backend-rendered templates.

## Styling Rules
- Prefer existing Angular styling patterns in the frontend workspace.
- Keep backend static asset changes (`apps/api/public`) only for backend assets like uploaded files or generated artifacts.

## Do Not
- Do not add new EJS templates or server-rendered pages in `apps/api`.
- Do not move Angular UI code into backend controllers/routes.
- Do not couple frontend component structure to backend internals.
